Let $ABCDE$ be a convex pentagon with the following properties: egin{itemize}\item $AB \parallel CE$\item $BC \parallel AD$\item $AC \parallel DE$\item $\angle ABC=120^\circ$\item $AB=3$\item $BC=5$\item $DE = 15$\end{itemize}Given that the ratio between the area of triangle $ABC$ and the area of triangle $EBD$ is $m/n$, where $m$ and $n$ are relatively prime positive integers, find $m+n$. egin{center} egin{tikzpicture}\draw (0,0) -- (3,0) -- (5,2) -- (2,4) -- (-3,4) -- cycle;\draw (0,0) -- (2,4) -- (5,2);
ode[below left] at (0,0) {$D$};
ode[below right] at (3,0) {$E$};
ode[above right] at (5,2) {$C$};
ode[above] at (2,4) {$B$};
ode[above left] at (-3,4) {$A$};
ode[above left] at (1,2) {$F$};
ode[above] at (4,1) {$5$};
ode[above left] at (1,2) {$3$};
ode[below] at (1.5,0) {$15$};\end{tikzpicture}\end{center}
